cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper is about unsupervised domain adaptation for semantic segmentation, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a novel method that uses multi-adversarial training to generate high-quality proxy labels for training on target data. This involves using discriminators to align features between the source and target domains, which is a technique commonly used in adversarial learning (cs.LG). The paper also incorporates confidence measures from both the class predictor and the adversarial discriminators, which involves using machine learning algorithms to make decisions based on uncertain or incomplete information (cs.AI). The proposed method is applied to semantic segmentation, which is a task that involves analyzing and understanding visual content, and can be considered a subfield of robotics (cs.RO) and multimedia (cs.MM).
